<div class="quotetitle">rainwarrior wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><br />Use this knowledge to make an NES port of Balance of Power.<br /></div><br />I mean this theorem doesn't apply only to countries on a map but can be generalized for any kind of 2D shapes.<br /><br />In other words, you can draw any set of shapes in a 2D plane with 4 colours, each shape being another colour than the shape next to it.<br /><br />I think this means you can draw anything on the NES, at least the shape of anything.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=38">Bregalad</a> — Tue May 22, 2012 12:59 am</p><hr />
