<id>http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=8918&amp;p=94180#p94180</id>
<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=8918&amp;p=94180#p94180"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Four colour theorem and NES graphics]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=8918&amp;p=94180#p94180"><![CDATA[
I didn't realise it until now, but there is a coincidence in the number of colours the NES can display with a single palette and the max. number of colours that is needed to distinguish arbitrary regions in a 2D plane.<br /><br />I'm not sure if this has any applications but I just discovered this coincidence and I'd like to know if anyone else ever noticed.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=38">Bregalad</a> — Mon May 21, 2012 9:10 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
